    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`formatprg` calls the formatting program, and pastes the `stderr` in the buffer.\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"985\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bdff4e51-e3fa-432a-8254-38237eb36c9a\" />\n\nAfter setting formatprg to `stylua -`, and typing `gggqG`\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"1008\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b658ed54-8cc6-4140-8ba9-d357d362dc82\" />\n\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\n echo \"local a: \" > test.lua\n nvim --clean test.lua\n```\n\n:lua vim.bo.formatprg=\"stylua -\"\ngggqG\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBuffer content should not be replaced with stderr. If the errcode of formatprg is non-0. Just do a `vim.notify`?\n\nI checked stylua's response by doing `cat test.lua | stylua - 2> err.out`. So it's clear that stylua isn't outputting errs to stdout.\n\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-167+g09d4eba92b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.2.280\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux fedora 6.19.8-200.fc43.x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20260321_093732_eea9aa79\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256-color\n\n### Installation\n\nmise",
